---
import { Image } from 'astro:assets';
import portrait from '@/assets/portrait/ahmed-hamdy-portrait-approved.webp';
import { withBase, contact } from '@config/site';

/**
 * §11 — About / career narrative. Uses the approved portrait (Gate 1 §13).
 * The portrait appears here and on Contact — never in the hero.
 *
 * Career-shift rule: this must not return the portfolio to a customer-support
 * identity. Close customer exposure is framed as the evidence source that made
 * the operational judgment possible.
 */
---

<section class="section zone-stone abt" id="about" aria-labelledby="abt-h">
  <div class="wrap abt__grid">
    <div class="abt__media">
      <Image
        src={portrait}
        alt="Ahmed Hamdy, Business Growth and Operations Specialist, in a dark suit and white shirt."
        widths={[280, 420, 560]}
        sizes="(max-width: 900px) 220px, 320px"
        loading="lazy"
        class="abt__img"
      />
      <div class="abt__meta">
        <div><span class="abt__k">Based in</span><span class="abt__v">Alexandria, Egypt</span></div>
        <div><span class="abt__k">Languages</span><span class="abt__v">Arabic (native) · English (professional)</span></div>
        <div><span class="abt__k">Education</span><span class="abt__v">Faculty of Al-Alsun, Ain Shams University — two academic years completed</span></div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="abt__body">
      <div class="sec-head" style="margin-bottom: var(--s5)">
        <span class="eyebrow">About</span>
        <h2 id="abt-h" class="sec-head__q">The path is the argument, not the thing to hide.</h2>
      </div>

      <div class="abt__prose">
        <p>
          I started close to customers — a high volume of them, remotely, inside a UK fintech
          environment. That is usually described as a starting point people move away from. I
          think it is the reason the rest of this works.
        </p>
        <p>
          Handling conversations at volume teaches something a report cannot: the difference
          between one unhappy customer and a process that will keep producing unhappy customers.
          The same question arriving three hundred times is not three hundred problems. It is one
          design failure, wearing a customer's voice.
        </p>
        <p>
          So I started tracing them backwards — to the article nobody could find, the policy that
          was never explained, the handoff nobody owned, the promise made upstream by a team that
          never saw the consequence. That habit turned into the work: diagnosing where a business
          loses value, and designing the smallest change that stops the loss.
        </p>
        <p>
          Formula4You is where the whole system came together at once. I saw a structural gap in
          Egypt's fragrance market — suppliers, manufacturers, brands, and customers scattered
          across social pages and messaging threads — and I did not solve it with a store. I
          designed a specialized platform: who participates, why they join, what they pay for,
          what order the launch has to happen in, and what deliberately does not get built.
        </p>
        <p class="abt__pull">
          I am not a marketer who learned operations, or a support specialist who learned
          strategy. I am someone who reads the whole system and can tell you which part of it is
          actually broken.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="cluster abt__ctas">
        <a class="btn btn--primary" href={withBase('/work/formula4you')}>Read the flagship case study</a>
        <a class="btn btn--ghost" href={contact.linkedin} rel="noopener">LinkedIn ↗</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .abt__grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 320px 1fr; gap: var(--s9); align-items: start; }
  @media (max-width: 900px) { .abt__grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: var(--s6); } }

  .abt__media { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: var(--s5); }
  .abt__img {
    width: 100%; height: auto; border-radius: var(--r-lg);
    border: 1px solid var(--hairline-stone);
  }
  @media (max-width: 900px) { .abt__img { max-width: 220px; } }
  .abt__meta { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: var(--s3); border-top: 1px solid var(--hairline-stone); padding-top: var(--s4); }
  .abt__meta div { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 2px; }
  .abt__k { font-family: var(--font-head); font-size: var(--fs-label); font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: 0.1em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--stone-muted); }
  .abt__v { font-size: var(--fs-caption); color: var(--stone-body); }

  .abt__prose { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: var(--s4); max-width: var(--measure); }
  .abt__prose p { color: var(--stone-body); }
  .abt__pull {
    font-family: var(--font-serif); font-style: italic;
    font-size: clamp(1.125rem, 1rem + 0.6vw, 1.375rem); line-height: 1.45;
    color: var(--stone-ink) !important;
    border-left: 3px solid var(--teal-deep); padding-left: var(--s5); margin-top: var(--s3);
  }
  .abt__ctas { margin-top: var(--s6); }
</style>
